{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the action space A expands to a joint action space A 1...N = A 1 × ⋯ × A N and the reward function ℜ to a set of reward functions = {ℜ 1,..., ℜ N }, where ℜ n ∶ S × A n → ℝ.",
    "This expansion necessitates the adjustment of the state transition distribution function, resulting in T ∶ S × A 1...N → P(S).",
    "Eventually, MG can be represented by the tuple < A, S, A 1...N, T,, 𝛾 >.",
    "In most cases, agents lack direct observation of the underlying state for optimal action selection, necessitating a mapping from observation history or belief states to actions.",
    "To address this challenge, some studies have extended the MG to a Partially Observable Markov Game (POMG) (Ma et al. 2021a)."
  ]
}